The '''Betsy Riot''' is a [[Far-left politics|radical left]] group that describes itself as a "decentralized neo-suffragette, punk-patriot resistance movement."<ref name="lincoln_banner">{{cite web |url=http://journalstar.com/news/state-and-regional/federal-politics/banner-in-lincoln-part-of-group-s-anti-trump-campaign/article_c5d36f57-3a47-5bb4-9629-55f0b0ff3648.html |title=Banner in Lincoln part of group's anti-Trump campaign |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=February 20, 2017 |website=Lincoln Journal Star |access-date=April 23, 2017}}</ref> They are [[Gun politics in the United States|pro-gun control]]. The group began in August 2016, primarily with an anti-gun industry focus,<ref name="roanoke_graffiti">{{cite web |url=http://www.roanoke.com/news/casey-roanoke-vandalism-gets-high-marks-from-new-anti-gun/article_d63bf193-d5e6-5adf-9429-93e796d46142.html |title=Casey: Roanoke vandalism gets high marks from new anti-gun group |last=Casey |first=Dan |date=August 31, 2016 |website=The Roanoke Times |access-date=April 23, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.virginiafirst.com/news/local-news/vandalism-found-outside-nra-office/543422640 |title=Vandalism found outside NRA office |last=Eskow |first=Kristen |date=August 2016 |website=Virginia First |access-date=April 23, 2017}}</ref> but since the [[United States presidential election, 2016|2016 presidential election]], has broadened its focus to protest [[Trump administration]] policies.<ref name="lincoln_banner"/> The group uses profanity, satire and a [[radical feminist]] posture in its messaging, with tactics that include graffiti,<ref name="roanoke_graffiti"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usnews.com/news/best-states/new-mexico/articles/2017-07-27/2-protesters-accused-of-vandalizing-new-mexico-gop-office |title=2 Protesters Accused of Vandalizing New Mexico GOP Office |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=July 27, 2017 |website=U.S. News & World Report |access-date=July 28, 2017}}</ref> theatrical protests,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://journalstar.com/news/local/protesters-show-support-for-abortion-rights/article_6ad70eb6-c33f-55d7-8b68-8199fba721c0.html |title=Protesters show support for abortion rights |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=February 11, 2017 |website=Lincoln Journal Star |access-date=April 23, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailynebraskan.com/image_6e4cc936-e12b-11e6-b7fc-97f134d6bb72.html |title=Betsy Riot, an anonymous, neo-sufferage group, waves signs in front of the Nebraska State Capitol at the Women's March Rally on Jan. 21, 2017|last=Ranard |first=Alyssa |date=January 22, 2017 |website=Daily Nebraskan |access-date=April 23, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.omaha.com/news/politics/protesters-shouting-do-your-job-and-meet-with-us-disrupt/article_762018e9-aaa3-539c-a4dc-5b6865567e99.html |title=Protesters shouting 'do your job' and 'meet with us' disrupt Deb Fischer's talk in Lincoln |last=Hammel |first=Paul |date=February 22, 2017 |website=Omaha World-Herald |access-date=April 23, 2017}}</ref> pranks, and coordinated messaging actions, such as mailings, banners,<ref name="lincoln_banner"/> and flyers.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.northplattebulletin.com/index.asp?show=news&action=readStory&storyID=33454&pageID=3 |title=Education chair draws fire from critics |last=Lauby |first=George |date=February 9, 2017 |website=North Platte Bulletin |access-date=April 23, 2017}}</ref> The group has also encouraged petty vandalism to further their agenda.

As part of an ongoing demonstration against gun rights advocates, Betsy Riot purchased http://johnlott.com/ ([[John Lott]]) and https://waynelapierre.com/ ([[Wayne LaPierre]]) and runs them as parody sites.

