A '''certificate of legal aid costs''' is a [[United Kingdom|British]] "certificate of costs allowed following taxation by a judicial or taxing officer."<ref>[http://www.hmcourts-service.gov.uk/infoabout/glossary/legal.htm Her Majesty's Courts Service official British Government web site] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080610015936/http://www.hmcourts-service.gov.uk/infoabout/glossary/legal.htm |date=2008-06-10 }}. Accessed May 5, 2008.</ref> <ref>[http://www.definition-legal.com/legal-terms.html Legal Definitions on line]{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}. Accessed May 5, 2008.</ref> <ref>[http://www.lawglossary.net/definition/682-Certificate_Of_Legal_Aid_Costs Law Glossary web site] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080527040505/http://www.lawglossary.net/definition/682-Certificate_Of_Legal_Aid_Costs |date=May 27, 2008 }}. Accessed May 5, 2008.</ref> <ref>[http://www.interdivorce.co.uk/glossary/c/certificate-of-legal-aid-costs.html Inter-divorce commercial web site] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071116075159/http://www.interdivorce.co.uk/glossary/c/certificate-of-legal-aid-costs.html |date=November 16, 2007 }}. Accessed May 5, 2008.</ref> It actually has nothing to do with [[legal aid]].
It is similar to a [[bill of costs]] used in [[Italy]],<ref>[http://www.romaone.it/statiche/linkcampus/docs/ItHandbook.pdf University of Milan at "Roma One" web site] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050228014447/http://www.romaone.it/statiche/linkcampus/docs/ItHandbook.pdf |date=February 28, 2005 }}. pdf document. Accessed May 5, 2008.</ref> and elsewhere.
